	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65028169"><p>Those calculations are very wrong, but they don't show their work so it's hard to be sure where they went wrong.  Nominal visual acuity (6/6, or 20/20 in freedom units) is being able to resolve things at about 60 points per degree.  Because people don't want to see pixels, display resolution should be about twice that.  That means 4k (3840 by 2180) should subtend not more than 32 degrees by 18 degrees.  An 8k display could be twice as large in each direction.</p><p>The trigonometry for display size is straightforw<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

