			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65027937"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65027937">Unfortunately, 1080p50/60 is not reliably supported in H.264 receivers, so the broadcast industry broadcasts in a hybrid mode called MBAFF which is 1080i50/60 but can include progressive frames to accommodate 1080p25/30. This allows them to broadcast both interlaced and progressive content in one stream.<br> <br>

H.265 receivers reliably support 50/60p even in 4K resolution so there is no interlaced in H.265.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65027937">

