	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65027939">There is no such thing as "2160i". 4K is broadcast in H.265, and H.265 decoders reliably support 50/60p even in 3840x2160. And generally, nobody broadcasts or encodes interlaced in H.265. Interlaced is theoretically supported by H.265 but it's neither reliably supported by decoders nor used by broadcaster.</div>
	</div>

